{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"119c5fb9-f7fd-49af-b03d-09bca1b611ca","content":"Here's what to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` package (xUnit v3) **or** if staying on xUnit v2, add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.XUnit` instead.\n\n3. **Add** this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with `dotnet test` as usual — it will use MTP under the hood.\n\n**Key notes:**\n- xUnit **v3** (`xunit.v3`) has native MTP support via `xunit.v3.runner.mtp`.\n- If you stay on xUnit **v2.9.3**, use the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.XUnit` bridge package instead.\n- The `TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport` property ensures `dotnet test` routes through MTP rather than VSTest.\n- You may also want to add `<UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>` to make `dotnet run` act as a test runner directly.\n\nWould you like help updating your `.csproj` file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d54a5555-f927-4fca-8205-88734f959e74","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":396,"requestId":"4815:23D333:30FACF5:358BAF4:69FBE23D"},"id":"c023ba63-df19-49b0-bc42-b1e6c7c93c5c","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:52:22.236Z","parentId":"f646be2b-6623-4036-a752-19a1ba6e81fa"}
